"Lets get you to medical quarters," Kenzo said as he helped 
Ravenchief to his feet and guided him inside.  On reaching the 
medical room he brought him to a CR chamber and opened it.  
"We'll need to run a diagnostic then we can start repairs." He 
explained.

--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, rm2kmidi <kraftlos@g...> wrote:
> Guardia closed the door of her room then ran to the front of the 
base. She 
> saw Ravenchief on the floor being helped by Kenzo.
>  "Are you ok?" asked Guardia.
>  Ravenchief gave a weak thumbs up then fell back down.
>  "I'm ok.... I guess. I got shot a couple of times, but nothing 
> permanent..."
>  "I think you should let Kenzo look at your injuries. You look 
terible."
>  As they sat there the heard the volley of weapons fire hitting 
the shields 
> outside. Unfortunately, the shields prevented the turrets from 
firing at the 
> enemies. So they would have to sit and wait for them to shut down, 
or 
> intentionally lower the shields so they could engage the enemy. 
>  Salveo rarely was put in this position. In the past, Lord Perseus 
had been 
> with them when they had had to deal with insurgents. This time he 
would have 
> to think of a plan on his own. He certainly hoped those Maximals 
outside 
> were on his side.
> 
>  On 9/6/05, Airly <airly2002@h...> wrote: 
> > 
> > Darkfate/Nightsrike:
> >  Nightstrike fired against the base as same as Darkfate
> >  Elita:
> >  Elita walked towards Guardia's room and came in she lie down in 
the bed 
> > and started to sob, all was her fault
> >   
> > "Just go into my room then, it should have my name on the door. 
I'll come 
> > back for you when the fighting is over." said Guardia.
> >  She waved goodbye and headed for the front of the base.
> > 
> >  On 9/6/05, Airly <airly2002@h...> wrote: 
> > > 
> > > Elita:
> > > "But... I don't have any room..."said Elita among sobs"I jsut 
arrive 
> > > here and... left and started all the mess"
> > > 
> > >  "That's.....good....." he said, then collapsing on the floor 
and going 
> > > unconscious.
> > >  ::Meanwhile::
> > >  Elita, can you go back to your room. I need to help them take 
care of 
> > > those bad people who were chasing us. Can you stay there until 
I come back 
> > > for you?" asked Guardia as they approached the barracks 
section of the base.
